<TITLE> Bangladesh to initiate SA Election Commissions Forum </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 26 (bdnews24.com)  A two-day meeting on formation of a forum of South Asian election commissions begins in Dhaka on Saturday. 'Meeting on Cooperation of Election Commissions in the South Asia Region' is the first of its kind and is being organised by Bangladesh's Election Commission, said EC secretary Muhammad Humayun Kabir. The meeting will be held at Dhaka's Radisson Water Garden Hotel with the participation of chief election commissioners (CEC) and secretaries of all SAARC countries other than Sri Lanka, the secretary said at the commission's office in Dhaka's Agargaon . Sri Lanka will not participate as their CEC post is currently vacant, Kabir added. The EC official also said the meeting aims to establish a forum for sharing electoral experiences, information and innovative strategies; alongside building institutional relations and long-term cooperation among all SAARC countries. He also said the meeting on its second day will concentrate on ways of forming the forum. The two-day meeting will discuss various issues including electoral systems in SAARC countries, recent experiences, Bangladesh's experience about voter registrations, role of poll management bodies in creating participation and publicity and funding of political parties. bdnew
